-- Kuwait Development Fund to Lend Serbian Rail $33 Million
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2012-10-22T07:34:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-22/kuwait-development-fund-to-lend-serbian-rail-33-million.html
Serbia’s state rail company
Zeleznice Srbije is expected to sign a 25 million-euro ($32.6
million) loan agreement with the Kuwait Development Fund next
month for the completion of a new station in Belgrade.  The Fund’s executive board is due to approve today the 18-
year loan, with a 3 percent interest rate and a four-year grace
period, the Serbian government said on its  website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
